[SN]TITLE[SN]
Nigel Williams named as A48 Caerwent fatal crash driver

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 55-year-old man who died after being hit by a car in Monmouthshire has been named by Gwent Police.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Nigel Williams, of Caerwent, was walking on the A48 near the Northgate House bed and breakfast in Caerwent when he was hit on Saturday at about 03:30 GMT.
He was taken to Newport's Royal Gwent Hospital, but died shortly after arrival.
The father-of-three's family said he would be "sadly missed".
"He always had time for everyone he met and was always ready to help with anything and everyone," they said.
Anyone who witnessed the crash has been asked to call Gwent Police on 101.
